4 SJR___ MOURNING THE DEATH AND CELEBRATING THE LIFE AND
5 LEGACY OF WILLIAM GRANT LYNCH, JR.
6
7 WHEREAS, it is with profound sorrow that we note the
8 passing of William Grant Lynch, Jr., longtime president and
9 chairman of Talladega Superspeedway and one of the most
10 respected leaders in NASCAR history, who departed this life
11 on October 2, 2025, at the age of 71; and
12 WHEREAS, William Grant Lynch, Jr. was born on October
13 23, 1953, in Rapid City, South Dakota, to Dr. William Grant
14 Lynch, Sr. and Sara McMichael Tyer; he was raised in
15 Winston-Salem, North Carolina, where he graduated from R.J.
16 Reynolds High School and later attended Lees-McRae College
17 and North Carolina State University; and
18 WHEREAS, Grant Lynch began his professional career
19 with R.J. Reynolds Tobacco Company's Marketing Enterprises,
20 where he worked for a decade and served as a key liaison
21 between NASCAR and its longtime Cup Series sponsor, helping
22 to strengthen one of the sport's most enduring partnerships;
23 and
24 WHEREAS, in 1993, he joined Talladega Superspeedway
25 as General Manager and was promoted to President later that
26 year, eventually serving as Chairman; during more than 26
27 years of leadership he guided the track through a
28 transformative era marked by growth and modernization, and
Page 1

transformative era marked by growth and modernization, and
SJR27 Enrolled
29 he strengthened relationships with fans, competitors, and
30 industry leaders; and
31 WHEREAS, under his direction, Talladega Superspeedway
32 underwent numerous enhancements, culminating in a
33 $50,000,000 infield transformation completed in 2019; that
34 same year the track celebrated its 50th anniversary season
35 and hosted the 100th NASCAR Cup Series race, for which Grant
36 Lynch served as Grand Marshal and delivered the command to
37 start engines before retiring later that year; and
38 WHEREAS, in recognition of his contributions to the
39 sport, Grant Lynch received NASCAR's Buddy Shuman Award in
40 2018 and also served as a Vice President of International
41 Speedway Corporation, overseeing the development and
42 construction of Kansas Speedway and Chicagoland Speedway;
43 and
44 WHEREAS, beyond motorsports, Grant Lynch was deeply
45 committed to the Talladega community, where he and his wife
46 raised their two daughters; he served on numerous civic and
47 charitable boards, including the Alabama Institute for Deaf
48 and Blind, the Antique Talladega Board, the Boy Scouts
49 Council, the Regions Bank Board, and the Talladega County
50 Economic Development Authority, frequently in leadership
51 roles; and
52 WHEREAS, his civic impact was especially evident at
53 the historic Talladega Ritz Theatre, where he served for
54 more than a decade as Board Chairman and helped expand arts
55 education, complete major capital improvements, and secure
56 long-term financial stability for the nationally recognized
Page 2

long-term financial stability for the nationally recognized
SJR27 Enrolled
57 Art Deco landmark; and
58 WHEREAS, following his retirement, Grant Lynch served
59 as President of the Alabama Wildlife Federation and remained
60 an avid outdoorsman; he was widely admired for his
61 larger-than-life personality, approachability, and genuine
62 love for people, earning a reputation as both a steward of
63 Talladega Superspeedway and a trusted friend to many; and
64 WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his mother, Sara
65 McMichael Tyer; he is survived by his loving wife, Marcia
66 Pfaff Lynch; children, Ashley Lynch Jackson (Chris) and Sara
67 Katherine Lynch; father and step-mother, Dr. William Grant
68 Lynch, Sr. and Ann Warren Lynch; sisters, Donna Lynch Sparks
69 (Dwight), Diane Lynch Herring (Steve), and Dawn Lynch Kucera
70 (Gary); and many nieces, nephews, extended family members,
71 and friends; and
72 WHEREAS, William Grant Lynch, Jr. will be remembered
73 for his vision, integrity, and enduring devotion to family,
74 community, and the sport of motorsports, and for helping to
75 shape Talladega Superspeedway into one of the most iconic
76 venues in the world; now therefore,
77 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
78 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That the death of William Grant
79 Lynch, Jr. is recorded with deep sadness, and this
80 resolution is offered in lasting tribute to his remarkable
81 life and service, with heartfelt sympathy extended to his
82 family, whose loss is shared by countless friends,
83 colleagues, and admirers.
